description:
Existence, Space and Architecture
Praeger | 1974 | English | 122 pages | PDF | 12 MB

The problem of architectural space has long demanded a new approach. Man must realize that he is not only the product of his environment, but its creator, and must learn to use this power with wisdom and imagination. The basic problem of space as a dimension of human existence is often ignored and the space-concept is discarded as out dated or even superfluous. The space concept, however, is particularly suited to the analysis of the human environment
